{
  "id": "lennox-xc21-txv",
  "brand": "Lennox",
  "model": "XC21-036",
  "equipment_type": "ac-condenser",
  "symptom": "Unit runs but cooling is poor. Suction line is frosted back to the compressor. Evaporator coil is partially iced. Superheat reads 2\u20134\u00b0F (far too low \u2014 spec is 8\u201312\u00b0F). Subcooling is normal or high.",
  "diagnosis": "TXV (thermostatic expansion valve) stuck open \u2014 overfeeding refrigerant to the evaporator. The sensing bulb may have lost its charge, or the valve itself is mechanically stuck. Flooding the compressor with liquid refrigerant \u2014 can cause slugging damage if not addressed.",
  "part_number": "R-410A TXV (aftermarket: Sporlan EBSE-5-GA or OEM Lennox 80W47) \u2014 must match tonnage and refrigerant",
  "procedure": [
    "Let the unit thaw completely before diagnostics \u2014 run the fan only for 20\u201330 minutes if iced.",
    "Connect gauges. Run the system and measure superheat at the suction line near the compressor.",
    "Normal superheat for this unit: 8\u201312\u00b0F. If reading <5\u00b0F, the TXV is overfeeding.",
    "Check the TXV sensing bulb \u2014 it should be securely strapped to the suction line at the 10 o'clock or 2 o'clock position, insulated from ambient air. A loose bulb can cause erratic behavior.",
    "If the bulb is properly mounted and superheat is still too low, the TXV is stuck open internally.",
    "Tap the TXV body with a wrench handle \u2014 occasionally this frees a stuck valve (temporary fix only).",
    "For permanent repair: recover refrigerant, braze out the old TXV, install the replacement (Sporlan EBSE-5-GA or Lennox 80W47).",
    "Mount the new sensing bulb at the correct position on the suction line. Insulate it.",
    "Pressure test, evacuate to 500 microns, recharge by weight.",
    "Run the system and verify superheat is in the 8\u201312\u00b0F range. Monitor for 15 minutes for stability."
  ],
  "safety_notes": [
    "Liquid refrigerant flooding back to the compressor can cause mechanical failure (slugging) \u2014 if superheat is near 0\u00b0F, shut the unit down immediately.",
    "Brazing near the evaporator coil requires nitrogen purge to prevent oxide formation inside the lines.",
    "If the coil is severely iced, water will drip during thaw \u2014 protect electrical components and the blower motor below."
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 90,
  "tags": [
    "TXV",
    "expansion valve",
    "low superheat",
    "iced coil",
    "frosted suction",
    "lennox",
    "XC21",
    "flooding",
    "liquid slugging"
  ],
